<TITLE> Putin says he will not let politics close markets </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sochi, Russia, Sep 19 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Prime Minister Vladimir Putin said on Friday Russia has no plans to close its markets for political reasons but sharply criticised what he described as other states' attempts to drag Russia back to the Cold War. "We view all attempts to drag us back into the Cold War era as nothing less than a direct threat to Russia's modernistion project," Putin told Russian officials and Western businessmen at an economic forum in the Black Sea resort of Sochi. Putin also said the government should aim to boost competition and cut the potential for market abuses by natural monopolies
